The first of them, Gallia Narbonensis, was an extension of the old Provincia possessed by Rome before the time of caesara conquesta. The next province had Lugdunum for its capital and was called from that fact Lugdunensis 3 its population was predominantly Celtic It embraced, roughly speaking, all the country from the valley of the Loire to that of the Seine, Normandy and Brittany being included in it The third province went by the old name of Aquitania It nowhere reached down to the Mediterranean, but embraced besides the, district south of the Garonne the country almost as far north as the left bank of the Loire.
